Date: 24 Aug 2001
From: "Karel Hruska" <hruska@vri.cz>

BSE in the Czech Republic, second cow suspected
-----------------------------------------------
A second cow (6 years old) in in one herd (19 heads) in Svetnov near Zdar,
in the Czech Republic, has been found positive for bovine spongiform
encephalopathy, the minister of agriculture announced today. The
confirmation of the diagnostic test is expected on Saturday (25 August).
The possible way of contamination is under investigation. Nearly 40 000
tests have been performed in the country this year.
--
K Hruska
<hruska@vri.cz>
VETERINARY RESEARCH INSTITUTE
Czech Republic
