[3
Date: 23 Aug 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhua News Agency, 22 Aug 2001 [edited

New case of mad cow disease in Denmark
--------------------------------------
STOCKHOLM: -- A 5 year old milk cow was diagnosed with BSE on 9 August in a
routine check-up on a farm in Ringsted, Denmark, the Danish Ministry of
Food, Agriculture and Fisheries said.
The cow was slaughtered after it tested positive and the cattle farm has
been isolated. The herd there will be slaughtered and burned to prevent a
further spread of the disease. This is the fourth reported case of BSE in
Denmark since February last year [2000.
